SUMMARY:WV Outdoor Economy Summit
DESCRIPTION:Hosted by The Nature Conservancy and the WVU Brad & Alys Smith Outdoor Economic Development Collaborative\, and proudly presented by the Charleston Convention & Visitors Bureau\, the West Virginia Outdoor Economy Summit is the state’s first cross-sector gathering focused on growing our $2.1 billion outdoor economy. \nJoin leaders from tourism\, conservation\, recreation\, entrepreneurship\, and community development on February 17–18\, 2026\, at the Charleston Coliseum & Convention Center\, to share ideas and shape West Virginia’s outdoor future. The momentum continues on February 19 at the State Capitol\, where we’ll showcase the strength and potential of West Virginia’s outdoor economy to lawmakers.
URL:https://wvbusinesslink.com/event/wv-outdoor-economy-summit/
LOCATION:Charleston Coliseum & Convention Center\, 200 Civic Center Dr\,\, Charleston\, WV\, 25301
CATEGORIES:Bridging Innovation,Business Training,Celebration,Conference,Entrepreneurs,Grants,hospitality,Human Resources,Innovators,Manufacturing,Marketing,Networking,Sales,social media,Summit,Supporting Entrepreneurs,tourism,Workforce
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://wvbusinesslink.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Screenshot-2025-08-15-at-2.45.37-PM.png
GEO:38.3564753;-81.6408384
X-APPLE-STRUCTURED-LOCATION;VALUE=URI;X-ADDRESS=Charleston Coliseum & Convention Center 200 Civic Center Dr Charleston WV 25301;X-APPLE-RADIUS=500;X-TITLE=200 Civic Center Dr\,:geo:-81.6408384,38.3564753
END:VEVENT
